 teams.</span></span></p>", ""], "授業外学習2": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">1. Rather than being taught, learn by your own will. It is more important for students to learn than for teachers to teach, so do your best. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">2. Ask lots of questions during class. It is important to ask questions whenever you don't understand something. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">3. Don't be late. Make sure to turn on your computer and log in to your computer and website before class starts. The classroom entrance will be locked every 10 minutes after the veil is lifted, so you cannot enter the classroom. If you knock on the door, 5 points will be deducted from your grade for the current class, so be sure not to be late. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">4. Read the materials on the website before coming to class. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">5. Meet the deadline for submitting assignments. Be careful, your assignments will not be graded if you do not submit them by the deadline. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">6. Be sure to submit your assignments by uploading them to the website. Be careful, you will not receive assignments by email. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">7. Back up your own assignments. You are responsible for managing your own backups. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">8. You may work on assignments in groups, but please submit unique content. Be careful, if you submit the exact same content as a group, everyone in the group will receive a negative mark. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">9. Before starting the assignment, make sure you understand the content and then work on it. If there is something you don't understand, be sure to ask questions. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">10. You are responsible for your own learning. Teachers will provide guidance to help you study, but it is your responsibility to study, so do your best. </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">11. You should ask lots of questions.</span></span>"}, "評価": {"0": "", "授業コード/Class code1": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code2": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code3": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code4": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code5": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code6": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code7": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code8": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code9": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code10": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code11": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code12": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code13": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code14": ["", ""], "授業コード/Class code15": ["", ""], "16": "", "参考文献・資料Reference books0": "Any Unity3D and Blender3D book in Japanese or English", "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": "No final exam. Students will be required to attend. There will be individual and team presentations. Media related homework such as videos, animations, sound, games, and other applications.", "学位授与の方針との関連Relationship to Diploma Policy1": "Each subject is placed on the curriculum based on the Diploma Policy (DP) and Curriculum Policy (CP) established by each faculty and graduate school.\nBy studying this subject with the DP and CP in mind, you will develop the abilities expected by each faculty and graduate school.\nThe DP, CP and curriculum table (list of subjects, etc.) of each faculty and graduate school are posted in the link below, so please use it as a referen